parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake accumulator failure can lead to a loss of braking power, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Engine suddenly loses all power
engine failure without warning
engine failure with no check engine lights or electronic error codes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inverter failure can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, increasing the risk of accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to serious injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident, as the airbags may not deploy or may deploy incorrectly, leaving occupants unprotected.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in an accident
airbag warning indicator is illuminated
airbags deploy unexpectedly
or airbags do not deploy correctly (e.g.
only some airbags deploy).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the passenger airbag indicator can lead to incorrect information about the airbag status, which may result in occupants being unaware of potential safety risks.
symptoms: Passenger airbag indicator is illuminated despite the passenger being above the airbag activation weight requirement
or the indicator is not illuminated when it should be.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The incorrect deployment of airbags can lead to injuries or fatalities, as occupants may be subjected to unnecessary forces or may not receive adequate protection in an accident.
symptoms: Airbags deploy unexpectedly
airbags do not deploy correctly (e.g.
only some airbags deploy)
or airbags deploy with excessive force.
